#: modules/health-monitor/traits/trait-onecom-texts.php:474
#: modules/health-monitor/traits/trait-onecom-texts.php:478
msgid "Disable user enumeration"
msgstr ""

#: modules/health-monitor/traits/trait-onecom-texts.php:475
msgid "One of the more common methods for bots and hackers to gain access to your website is to find out login usernames and brute force the login area with tons of dummy passwords. The hope is that one the username and password combos will match, and voilà - they have access (you'd be surprised how common weak passwords are!)."
msgstr ""

#: modules/health-monitor/traits/trait-onecom-texts.php:476
msgid "There are two sides to this hacking method - the username and the password. The passwords are random guesses, but (unfortunately) the username is easy to get. Simply typing the query string ?author=1, ?author=2 and so on, will redirect the page to /author/username/ - bam, the bot now has your usernames to begin brute force attacks with."
msgstr ""

#: modules/health-monitor/traits/trait-onecom-texts.php:477
msgid "This security recommendation locks down your website by preventing the redirect, making it much harder for bots to get your usernames. We highly advise actioning this recommendation."
msgstr ""

